# Database Schema Design

## Tables

### Patient
- id (PK, UUID)
- name (VARCHAR)
- age (INT)
- gender (VARCHAR)
- phone (VARCHAR)
- address (VARCHAR)

### Doctor
- id (PK, UUID)
- name (VARCHAR)
- specialization (VARCHAR)
- phone (VARCHAR)

### Appointment
- id (PK, UUID)
- patient_id (FK → Patient.id)
- doctor_id (FK → Doctor.id)
- appointment_date (TIMESTAMP)
- notes (TEXT)

### Prescription
- id (PK, UUID)
- appointment_id (FK → Appointment.id)
- medication (VARCHAR)
- dosage (VARCHAR)
- instructions (TEXT)
